HEADWORD: Atlantean
<hw>At`lan*te"an</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Atlant⟦emac⟧us</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to
the isle Atlantis, which the ancients allege was sunk, and overwhelmed
by the ocean.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Pertaining to, or resembling, Atlas;
strong.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With <qex>Atlantean</qex> shoulders, fit to bear⟦br⟧
The weight of mightiest monarchies.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Atlantes</ent>⟦br⟧
